      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46), an uncompromising example of Bavarian engineering. At its heart lies the S54 high-revving straight-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a precision-tuned VANOS system. This unit has been meticulously maintained with documented rod bearing service and a reinforced rear subframe to ensure structural integrity under high lateral G-loads. The 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox offers tactile engagement, paired with a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential for optimal mechanical grip. Suspension geometry remains factory-spec, providing the telepathic steering response these chassis are known for. With flawless paint depth and a pristine Nappa leather cabin, this is a definitive collector's piece.",
